ZCZC OE74
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE IS CENTRED 1025 OVER IRELAND WITH LOW
PRESSURE ACROSS SCANDINAVIA AND THE FAR W OF THE ATLANTIC. THERE IS LITTLE
CHANGE TO THE SYNOPTIC PATTERN OVERNIGHT. DURING SUNDAY MORNING THE HIGH
PRESSURE GENERALLY PERSISTS BUT SLWY SINKS SWARDS TO REACH 1025 OVER FASTNET
BY MIDDAY. INTO MONDAY A CYCLONIC PATTERN MOVS ACROSS NERN PARTS OF PORTPATRICK
SQUEEZING THE HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE FURTHER SWARDS WHILST A SECOND HIGH PRESSURE
CENTRE FORMS OVER THE NORWEGIAN SEA. THIS HIGH RECEDES OVERNIGHT AS A LOW
PRESSURE AREA FORMS W OF ICELAND WHILST THE HIGH PRESSURE OVER CULLERCOATS
AND NITON PERSISTS UNTIL THE END OF THE PERIOD. STRG WINDS FORMING FOR PARTS
OF SHANNON ROCKALL HEBRIDES FAEROES AND S E ICELAND ON MONDAY POSSIBLY
EXTENDING ACROSS BAILEY AND FAIR ISLE ON TUESDAY. HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE NOT
EXP ACROSS SEERN PARTS OF PORTPATRICK
